-epistemology. It provides a pragmatist, social and functionalist account of epistemic states that offers the conceptual space for revised or even replaced epistemic concepts. This is what it means to "refurbish epistemology": The book assesses conceptual tools in relation to epistemology’s functionally defined conceptual space, responsive to both intra-epistemic considerations and political and moral values.   aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Aug 2020) 0aKnowledge, Theory of. 4aFeministische Epistemologie. 4aFunktionalismus. 4aKuhn, Thomas S. 4aNormativität. 4aSocial epistemology. 4aSoziale Epistemologie. 4aThomas S. Kuhn. 4afeminist epistemology. 4afunctionalism. 4anormativity. 7aPHILOSOPHY / Epistemology.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus eBook-Package 2017z978311071954308iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2017z9783110540550oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE ENGLISH 2017z978311062526408iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Philosophy 2017z9783110548228oZDB-23-DPH0 cEPUBz97831105246590 cprintz978311051941940uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311052545840uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110525458423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9783110525458.jpg  a978-3-11-062526-4  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE ENGLISH 2017b2017  a978-3-11-071954-3  DG Plus eBook-Package 2017b2017  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK  aZDB-23-DGGb2017  aZDB-23-DPHb2017